comment: The full-eta axiom for the surreal numbers. This is the single most important property of the surreals. It says that, given two sets of surreals such that one comes completely before the other, there is a surreal lying strictly between the two. Furthermore, there is an upper bound on the birthday of that surreal. Alling's axiom FE. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 7-Dec-2021.)
